<section id="References_oVirt_3_Directory_Firewall_Requirements">
   <title>Directory Firewall Requirements</title>
	<para>
		oVirt requires a directory server to support user authentication. Currently the supported directory servers are <acronym>IPA</acronym> and Active Directory. Both require a number of ports to be opened in the directory server's firewall to support <acronym>GSS-API</acronym> authentication as used by the oVirt Engine.
	</para>
